snippet: One Russian separatist leader is said to be trying to unite the mishmash of militias into a single professional fighting force, while the national military prepares to attempt to retake the rebel stronghold of Donetsk.
abstract: Motley mix of separatist rebel groups in eastern Ukraine is complicating the already difficult task of getting peace talks off the ground.

byline.original: By SABRINA TAVERNISE and DAVID M. HERSZENHORN
byline.contributor: Sabrina Tavernise reported from Donetsk, and David M. Herszenhorn from Kiev, Ukraine.

lead_paragraph: One Russian separatist leader is said to be trying to unite the mishmash of militias into a single professional fighting force, while the national military prepares to attempt to retake the rebel stronghold of Donetsk.

headline.main: Patchwork Makeup of Rebels Fighting Ukraine Makes Peace Talks Elusive
headline.print_headline: Patchwork Makeup of Rebels Fighting Ukraine Makes Peace Talks Elusive
